{"key":"post-13748436","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13748436</id>\n<content>You should stir the grains.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you're breaking too many kernels doing so, it sounds like the pot isn't large enough for the amount of grains you're using.&amp;nbsp; I use a large wooden spoon.&amp;nbsp; Don't scrape the spoon across the bottom of the pan, but rather 'row' with it, causing turbulence which lifts the grains that are trying to stick to the bottom.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13750756</next>\n<prev>13748401</prev>\n<first>13746496</first>\n<last>13750795</last>\n<when>1294441623</when>\n<utime>01/08/11 01:07 AM</utime>\n</post>"}